AGI -&nbsp; New York mayor Eric Adams> defended the artificial intelligence used by the municipal services charged for providing business councils that broke the law. Launched in October as a pilot project, the chatbot MyCity > was presented as a "reliable" software to ask for advice on how to carry out economic activities, but at practical time it would fall into a series of Marche errors and civil code. Journalists of the website The Markup reported, last week, the presence of some wrong answers provided to users: in a MyCity considered the possibility of cutting tips to employees and asserted the absence of employers' obligations in pre-adverting employees of changes in work shifts. In both cases, it was not true.&nbsp;
